<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911120-0138</DOCNO><DOCID>911120-0138.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing andamp; Media:   New Burger King TV Ads   Will Attack McDonald's</HL><DATE>11/20/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   DIS GRM MCD PEP</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>ADVERTISING, MARKETING, PUBLIC RELATIONS (ADV)BEVERAGES (BVG)ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)FOOD PRODUCTS (FOD)MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY (REC)RESTAURANTS, FAST-FOOD, CATERING (RES)SOFT DRINKS, MAKERS OF NON-ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES (SFT)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)EUROPE (EU)ILLINOIS (IL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   ORLANDO, Fla. -- Burger King Corp. bashes McDonald's Corp.in a series of television commercials that will start airingnext week.   &quot;We serve individuals, not billions,&quot; the ads say, takinga shot at the &quot;billions and billions served&quot; claim thatadorns McDonald's golden arches signage world-wide. The spotsdrew prolonged applause when several were shown at BurgerKing's franchisee convention here yesterday.</LP><TEXT>   The commercials expand on the fast-food chain's &quot;Your way. . . right away&quot; marketing theme with the additional line,&quot;Whaddaya say, whaddaya say?&quot; The D'Arcy Masius Benton andamp;Bowles advertising agency produced the ads.   Burger King also has signed TV personality and pitchmanWillard Scott for commercials promoting its breakfast menu.Those spots will air early next year, as the company rollsout a breakfast burrito to compete with similar items fromMcDonald's and PepsiCo Inc.'s Taco Bell unit. Burger King isa unit of Grand Metropolitan PLC.   Next week Burger King will launch a promotional tie-inwith Walt Disney Co.'s new animated film, &quot;Beauty and theBeast,&quot; by featuring character figures with Kids' Meals.</TEXT></DOC>